<!DOCTYPE html>
<%# Type: dynamic
		Catorgory: error %>
<html lang="en-US">

<head>
	<title>Clutter -- Not Found</title>
	<%- include("headTag") -%>
</head>

<body>
	<%- include("header") -%>
	<div id="content">
		<center id="notfound"><img src="/img/errors/Dark-Taco.svg" alt="Dark Wizard Taco" width="600" id="darkWizardTaco">
		<h1>404 - Not Fount</h1>
		What <span style="font-style:italic;font-weight:bold;font-size:20px">black magic</span> is this?!<br>The server couldn't find or access <% if (type == 1) { %>the Clutter by the id of<% } else if (type == 2) { %>the user by the name of<% } %> <span class="path"><%= path %></span>.
		<% if (path.length > 25) { %><br>Well... what did you think would happen if you typed in a url <span style="font-style:italic;font-weight:bold;font-size:20px">that</span> long?<% } %></center>
	</div>
	<script>
		let image = document.getElementById("darkWizardTaco")
		window.onresize = () => {
			checkImage()
		}
		function checkImage() {
			if (screen.width < 450) {
				image.width = screen.width - 30
			} else {
				image.width = 450
			}
		}
		checkImage()
	</script>
	<%- include("footer") -%>
	<script type="text/javascript" src="/script.js"></script>
</body>

</html>